Cursor-based pagination is more stable than offset-based pagination because it paginates based on actual data values instead of row positions, reducing duplication or missing records when inserts happen.

##
🧠 First Understand the Core Difference
1️⃣ Offset Pagination

Used by gems like will_paginate

It says:

Skip N rows, then give me next 10

Example:

SELECT * FROM users
ORDER BY id ASC
LIMIT 10 OFFSET 10;

Meaning:

Skip first 10 rows

Return next 10 rows

⚠️ Important: It depends on row position, not actual data values.

2️⃣ Cursor Pagination

It says:

Give me records after this specific record value

Example:

SELECT * FROM users
WHERE id > 10
ORDER BY id ASC
LIMIT 10;

⚠️ Important: It depends on actual data value, not row number.

